  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F. ",
    "Season the beef strips with salt, black pepper, and chili flakes. ",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together pineapple juice, fish sauce, lime juice, brown sugar, and garlic. ",
    "Add the beef to the marinade and mix to coat. ",
    "Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and arrange the beef in a single layer. ",
    "Roast in the preheated oven for 12 minutes. ",
    "While the beef is roasting, heat a wok or large skillet over high heat. ",
    "Add the ginger and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly. ",
    "Add the cilantro, peanuts, and a pinch of salt. ",
    "Stir-fry for 1 minute. ",
    "Add the roasted beef to the wok and stir-fry for 2-3 minutes, until crispy. ",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional cilantro and peanuts if desired."
  ],
